      passage: `The Federalist Papers are a collection of 85 essays by Alexander Hamilton, John Jay, and James Madison. Their publication (under a single pen name) was divided among the Daily Advertiser and other New York newspapers in 1787–88. Though the authorship of most of the individual essays is certain, that of a few is in question: while No. 6, “Concerning Dangers from Dissensions between the States,” was surely penned by Hamilton, No. 62, “The Senate,” may have been written by either Hamilton or Madison.`,
